{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1774458147,"nonce":"enNEyaRHV8DxCF26hXVI5zhUYNM=","title":"Part 2 analysis: fixed points during reaching","message":"Umbrella: 0af472c (Part 2)\n\n**Motivation:** Understand the dynamical landscape the RNN traverses during reaching. Fixed points and their stability reveal how the network organizes its state space for movement generation, and how SISU modifies this landscape.\n\n**Approach:** Find fixed points of the RNN dynamics at each timestep along reaching trajectories using optimization-based FP finding (from feedbax `FixedPoints`). Uses PCA for dimensionality reduction, with candidates drawn from trajectory windows around each timestep. Crossed with SISU levels and perturbation amplitudes.\n\n**Status:** Module exists at `src/rlrmp/modules/analysis/part2/fps_reach.py`. Implements candidate extraction (windowed and simple), PCA dependency, and vmapped FP finding. Several planned analyses (PC trajectory plots, tangling, Jacobians/Hessians at FPs) are commented out as TODOs.\n\n**References:** Sussillo \u0026 Barak (2013) for RNN fixed point analysis; Kaufman et al. (2014) for dynamics during reaching.","files":null}]}